redcap:Alerts.email_subject: PSU Sponsorship of External Collaborator [first_name] [last_name] of [ext_org] for REDCap Use
redcap:Alerts.alert_message:
[first_name] [last_name] of [ext_org], (PSU Username: [psu_one_id_ex]) is requesting a REDCap account. In order for them to use REDCap, they will need a PSU sponsored account.

  1. Visit the Sponsored Account Management System
  2. Log in with your PSU credentials (i.e. abc1234),
  3. Click the yellow "+" button
  4. Use the "Search Existing Accounts" option to add [first_name] [last_name] and select the name. If the name does not exist:
    • contact [first_name] [last_name], [email] to create a PSU Account.
    • Otherwise, click Next
      • When account is displayed correctly, click Next
      • Category: REDCap 2FA
      • Expiration date: enter an expiration date up to 365 days
      • Program Name: REDCap
      • Program Contact Information: your email
      • Click Next
      • Enabled Services: Verify that only Authentication has been selected
      • Click Next
      • Accept all defaults except change your Contact Email Address if needed.
      • Click Sponsor button
      • Click Done

If you receive an Access Denied page. You will need to request sponsorship privileges by visiting the Penn State New Sponsored Account Owner Request, log in with your PSU credentials (i.e. abc1234), then click on Agree to the responsibilities and click on the "Order Now" button. It could take up to 7 days for approval. You will be notified by email from the Service Desk when your account is approved for sponsorship permission. This process is only needed once for any number of accounts you wish to sponsor.

Thank you,

REDCap Administrator

The training consists of a Detailed Overview for a total time of 14 minutes. This video was created by Vanderbilt University and may look slightly different than the PSU version of REDCap but is still accurate for training purposes.
After you view the video, there is a 10 question quiz. Please complete the quiz with an 80% or better. If you do not complete the quiz with an 80% or better score, you will be given the opportunity for up to 5 more tries however some of the questions will be different than the prior quizzes.
Please click on Submit to start the tutorial.

Question.TranslatedText: Question: Can REDCap database projects be accessed from anywhere at any time on any device with an internet connection and an account? Answer: Yes, REDCap can be access from anywhere with an internet connection on any computer, tablet, and phone.
Question.redcap:FormattedTranslatedText: Question: Can REDCap database projects be accessed from anywhere at any time on any device with an internet connection and an account? Answer: Yes, REDCap can be access from anywhere with an internet connection on any computer, tablet, and phone.

Question.TranslatedText: Question: Each REDCap system is independent and managed by an individual institutional partner configuring the system to the institutional needs. Answer: Yes, every REDCap installation is managed by the individual institution which will have policies and procedures for configuring the system and use cases.

Question.TranslatedText: Question: Project Setup page is a checklist of tasks to help build and test your project. Which task is NOT part of Project Setup. Answer: Complete the project; this is a feature you would use when your project has been completed and you wish to remove it from your active projects list. Question.TranslatedText: Question: All changes in a Production mode project will: Answer: Be reviewed for data loss, only changes in Development mode will take effect immediately

Question.TranslatedText: Question: Which feature will assist you with building your instruments? Answer: Online Designer; Reporting allows you to look at your data already collected and Data Entry forms are for data entry, not form design.

Question.TranslatedText: Question: What are the two required settings to create a field? Answer: Field label and Variable name; REDCap requires you to enter data in these two sections of field creation. Validation, required tag and identifier tag are optional

Question.redcap:FormattedTranslatedText: Question: For multiple choice questions, the numerical value of the choice is displayed during data entry. Answer: False, the choice label is displayed during data entry

Question.TranslatedText: Question: When is the best time to test your instruments? Answer: In Development mode, frequently during the building of your project; it is always a best practice to test and test often during the building of your project in Development mode.
Question.redcap:FormattedTranslatedText: Question: When is the best time to test your instruments? Answer: In Development mode, frequently during the building of your project; it is always a best practice to test and test often during the building of your project in Development mode.
